The paper deals with the problem of indexing and retrieving documents from large string collections, which is a classic information retrieval (IR) problem. Therefore, cs.IR is the most likely sub-category. The paper also introduces novel data structures and algorithms for compressing and querying repetitive string collections, which involves techniques from data structures (cs.DS), deep learning (cs.DL), databases (cs.DB), and computational complexity (cs.CC).
